{{Class 5|hexagon=<span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span>|color-l=20%|color-s=25%|color-h=12|class=Euler|safety=Unpredictable|entity=Cognitohazardous|security=Reality-Bending}}

'''Level <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span>'''  is a sub-level between [[Level 2]] and [[Level 3]].
==<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⤳ Description</span>==
'''Level <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span>''' (pronounced ''Euler'') resembles a large expanse of terrain, consisting of two areas: a large forest and a courtroom. The level is named after the same mathematical constant <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e.</span>
===<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⮡ㅤArea 1: "Forest of Math" ⮢</span>===
{{Blurimage|file=LevelEulerForest.png|hovertext=The Mathenatical Forest|caption=A photograph of Level <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span>, in the ''Forest of Math''.}}
The first area of Level <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span> is designated as the '''''Forest of Math'''''. The ''Forest of Math'' is an endless forest, although it has multiple non-Euclidean properties and mathematical oddities. The forest itself seems to be in a forever autumn-like state, as it has never been known to change itself into other seasons.<ref>The time of day also never changes in the level.</ref> The farther you go into the forest, the more geometrically unstable it becomes. Similarly to [[Level 11]], the trees can occasionally depict repetitive geometry. Any attempts to wander the forest in a linear way have been proven to be extremely unstable as the forest frequently distorts itself.<ref>The forest distorts itself every 10 to 20 minutes.</ref> After wandering for a period of time, wanderers may come across an unusually large room situated in the middle of the forest, which leads to Area 2.
====<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⮡  Anomalies ⮢</span>====
{{Blurimage|file=LevelEulerForest2.png|hovertext=The Mathenatical Forest|caption=Another photograph in the ''Forest of Math''. This time, trees are depicting repetitive geometry and are non-Euclidean.}}
Mathematical anomalies are present within the forest the further you go down the forest, with each anomaly becoming more drastic the further down a wanderer goes. These include:
