It is believed that many more anomalies exist within the forest.
</div>
<br><br><br>
<div style="background-color: black; border: solid 4px white; padding: 20px 40px; font-family: Sofia Sans; font-size: 20px; border-radius: 8px; display: inline-block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; width: 100%; height: 50%; color: white;">
===<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⮡ㅤArea 2: "The Auditorium" ⮢</span>===
{{Blurimage|file=LevelEulerAuditorium.jpg|hovertext=The Auditorium|caption=A variant of ''The Auditorium'', showing a presentation.}}
{{Blurimage|file=LevelEulerAuditorium2.jpg|hovertext=The Auditorium|caption=Another variant of ''The Auditorium'', this time having a more liminal aesthetic.}}
'''''The Auditorium''''' is the second area of Level <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span>. ''The Auditorium'' is a simple auditorium situated in the ''Forest of Math'', though its location is randomized — it could be within the premises when a wanderer first spawns, or it could be in a place to a certain extent that a wanderer could not reach it by any means possible. The Auditorium is shown differently to every wanderer, making each auditorium personalized. ''The Auditorium'' itself has no anomalies similar to those in the forest, albeit there are exclusive anomalies that are not found within the forest.
====<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⮡  Anomalies ⮢</span>====
Multiple anomalies are found within ''The Auditorium''. These include:<br>
*A forever looping speech
*Certain objects not casting shadows, most commonly [[Object 1|Almond Water]]<ref>This also includes irregular shadows, in where some shadows looks like a humanoid figure.</ref>
*The exit door (which is the main exit to the level) being situated on weird areas, most notably on the ceiling or on the ground
*Sitting in certain chairs will cause the floor to seemingly "sink"
*The auditorium seemingly "stretching", in where more and more rows appear behind wanderers<ref>It is believed that the rows could be infinite.</ref>
*A perfect circular hole in the ceiling, where if looked at reveals an identical auditorium above you, and what appears to be an identical you looks back
====<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⮡  History ⮢</span>====
It is believed that the speech that loops itself is actually a group of gods conversing with regular wanderers. Wanderers claim to undergo an "enlightenment" period, and become one of the "Beautiful People". Because of this, it is heavily believed that ''The Auditorium'' was once a death cult full of gods using its powers.
</div>
<br><br><br>
<div style="background-color: black; border: solid 4px white; padding: 20px 40px; font-family: Sofia Sans; font-size: 20px; border-radius: 8px; display: inline-block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; width: 100%; height: 50%; color: white;">
==<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⤳ Entities</span>==
Level <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">e</span> is entirely devoid of life. However, due to the anomaly of mathematical concepts being physical entites, it causes confusion within many wanderers.
</div>
<br><br><br>
<div style="background-color: black; border: solid 4px white; padding: 20px 40px; font-family: Sofia Sans; font-size: 20px; border-radius: 8px; display: inline-block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; width: 100%; height: 50%; color: white;">
==<span style="font-family: Sofia Sans; font size: 50px">⤳ Entrances & Exits</span>==
=== ⮡ㅤEntrances ⮢ ===
The only known entrance is to say the first ten digits of Euler's constant with absolute perfection — doing so will lead here.<ref>This does not work in certain inescapable or "dead end" levels, such as [[Level 87]].</ref>
=== ⮡ㅤExits ⮢ ===
*Going through the exit door in ''The Auditorium'' will lead to a random level.
*Phasing through reality via anomalies will also lead to a random level.
*Finding a window with the layout of [[Level Pi|Level π]] and going through it will take you to said level.
</div>
